---
globs: web/public/**, web/scripts/**, netlify.toml
alwaysApply: false
---

VAIFORM — WEB / NETLIFY / CALLER RULES

Applies to:
- web/public/**
- web/scripts/**
- netlify.toml

Rules:
- Browser callers must use same-origin /api/* only.
- Do not call hardcoded backend origins from web/public.
- Do not add _redirects under web/.
- Do not reintroduce Vite/Rollup or a new build pipeline unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve current caller-consumed response field names.
- Keep frontend logic consuming backend truth, not recreating it.
- For preview/storyboard/render UI work:
  - do not recreate backend timing truth in the frontend
  - consume playbackTimelineV1 / previewReadinessV1
  - do not weaken preview parity
  - keep UI/layout changes scoped to UI unless contract changes are explicitly approved
